---------------------------------------------------
Script Contents
---------------------------------------------------
Notes_cleanser_v1.py
FirstNameDatabase.csv
LastNameDatabase.csv


---------------------------------------------------
Version
---------------------------------------------------
16/07/19 v1 Jerry Chen (jche318@gmail.com) Initial version


---------------------------------------------------
Description
---------------------------------------------------
Script expects an excel file "Analysis_Latest_Test.xlsx" in same directory and a column named "Note" which holds the notes in Sheet1. 
It outputs a "output.csv" file with a flattened version of the excel with matched first name, last names replaced with Joe, Bloggs 
respectively in the Note column.


---------------------------------------------------
Instructions for Windows
---------------------------------------------------
1. Unzip to folder
2. Open CMD and navigate to directory
3. One-off verify python 3.* installed (https://www.python.org/downloads/)
4. One-off verify pandas installed ("pip3 install pandas")
5. One-off verify xlrd installed ("pip3 install xlrd")
6. Enter "python3 Notes_cleanser_v*.py"


---------------------------------------------------
Notes
---------------------------------------------------
- use of python3/pip3 or python/pip command is interchangable depending on your installation configuration
- If your python version does not retrieve XLRD causing an error for pandas to read the Excel file, it can be installed using "pip3 install xlrd"